# Modern UI & 3D Component Integration Plan

The goal is to transform the existing [Dashboard.jsx](file:///d:/project/Smart%20Expense%20Manager/client/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx) and [Expenses.jsx](file:///d:/project/Smart%20Expense%20Manager/client/src/pages/Expenses.jsx) into a premium, modern, and highly interactive user interface. We will draw inspiration from top-tier UI libraries like PrebuiltUI, utilizing Tailwind CSS for glassmorphism, gradients, and micro-animations.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **New Dependencies:** Installed `three`, `@react-three/fiber`, and `@react-three/drei` to render 3D component. Installed `framer-motion` for smooth UI micro-animations.
> - **Visual Style:** The new design features a modern premium light mode with rich purple accents and highly stylised shadows (`shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.04)]`).

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
#### [MODIFY] package.json
- Add `three`, `@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`
- Add `framer-motion`

***

### Components
#### [NEW] src/components/ThreeDElement.jsx
- A reusable 3D component using React Three Fiber.
- Renders a slow-rotating 3D object next to the dashboard welcome text.

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/Dashboard.jsx
- **Header:** Transformed into a clean white header with 3D elements and vibrant stats.
- **Charts:** Fully interactive Doughnut and Line charts styled properly for the light theme context.
- **Transactions list:** Premium design mimicking exact "ExpenseTrack" layout.

#### [MODIFY] src/pages/Expenses.jsx (Phase 5)
- **Top Summary:** Search bar + Categorization Dropdowns.
- **Sidebar Details:** Total expenses this month card (purple gradient) + Category Breakdown.
- **Main List:** Fully redesigned list structure avoiding basic table wrappers, instead opting for a grid-based card layout.

#### [NEW] src/pages/Budget.jsx (Phase 6)
- **Top Cards:** Summary trackers for Overall Budget, Spent, and Status.
- **List:** Dynamic Progress Bar listings per category.
- **Insights Sidebar:** Custom Red alert box, Monthly insights, and bar graph.

#### [NEW] src/pages/Analytics.jsx (Phase 7)
- **Charts:** Weekly/Monthly dual Bar Chart and Financial Health Doughnut.
- **Data Tables:** Ranked list of categories with inline progress bars.

#### [NEW] src/pages/Landing.jsx (Phase 8)
- **Marketing Page:** A premium public landing page with Hero, Features, Testimonials, and a custom CSS-only browser UI mockup.
- **Routing:** Changed `/` to render `<Landing />` instead of a redirect to login.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Local Tests
1. **Dependencies Installation:** Verify that `npm install` runs successfully without conflicts.
2. **Build Test:** Run `npm run build` to ensure the 3D libraries and Motion don't break the Vite build.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the app in the browser (`http://localhost:5173`).
2. Navigate to the Dashboard.
3. Check UI layouts in the ExpenseTrack screen.
